There is a bootstrap issue at the moment to build the server
you first need to compile psycopg2-2.0.6:
% cd third_party/src
% tar zxvf psycopg2-2.0.6.tar.gz
% cd psycopg2-2.0.6
% python setup.py build
% mv build/lib.linux-i686-2.4/psycopg2 ../../python/

Add the following lines to the server's instinctual.ini file:
debug: true
db_engine: postgresql_psycopg2
db_name: informer




1) set up the vhost files:
% cd conf
% cp ~/TEMPLATE_vhost.conf vhost.conf
% ln vhost.conf vhost_ssl.conf

2) run MT reconfig:
% /usr/local/psa/admin/sbin/websrvmng --reconfigure-vhost --vhost-name=<HOST>

3) create media symlinks:
% cd httpdocs
% ln -s ../informer/third_party/python/django/contrib/admin/media/
% ln -s ../informer/media site_media

% cd httpsdocs
% ln -s ../informer/third_party/python/django/contrib/admin/media/
% ln -s ../informer/media site_media

4) give apache write permissions to upload
% chmod g+w media

5) Add informer to apache, psaserv groups
% vi /etc/group

6) create the database
% createdb -U <username> <dbname>

-
